In addition to any other information the Commission may require by regulation, the medical care data base shall:
Collect for each type of patient encounter with a health care practitioner or facility designated by the Commission:
The demographic characteristics of the patient;
The principal diagnosis;
The procedure performed;
The date and location of where the procedure was performed;
The charge for the procedure;
If the bill for the procedure was submitted on an assigned or nonassigned basis;
If applicable, a health care practitioner's universal identification number; and
If the health care practitioner rendering the service is a certified registered nurse anesthetist or certified nurse midwife, identification modifiers for the certified registered nurse anesthetist or certified nurse midwife;
Collect appropriate information relating to prescription drugs for each type of patient encounter with a pharmacist designated by the Commission; and
Collect appropriate information relating to health care costs, utilization, or resources from payors and governmental agencies.

section.section:
On an annual basis, the Commission shall publish:
The total reimbursement for all health care services over a 12-month period;
The total reimbursement for each health care specialty over a 12-month period;
The total reimbursement for each code over a 12-month period; and
The annual rate of change in reimbursement for health services by health care specialties and by code.
